ABCs of Behavior [id=fba2_abc_section]
-----------------

Annie: Alright, I think I get it now. But didn't Lianne say that we had to do something else to figure out the function of behavior?

Lin: Right, we had to look at what came before the behavior and then what came after the behavior.

JJ: Yes, the antecedent, then the behavior, then the consequences.

Annie: Oh, that's right, I remember now. The professor said, "It's as easy as learning your ABCs!"

Teaching ABCs with AI [id=fba2_abc_teaching]
----------------------

Annie: Let's ask AI to help us better understand the ABCs.

::fba2_ai_abc_diagrams [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Create ABC Diagrams with AI"]

--- wait @fba2_ai_abc_response.value ---

Scaffolding ABCs [id=fba2_abc_scaffold]
-----------------

::fba2_abc_reference [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="View ABC Reference Diagrams"]

JJ: I remember this from my notes. Let's look at the first box. The Antecedent is the thing that happens before the behavior. That's the yellow box. The teacher gives a difficult task... [face=explaining]

Lin: Right, which leads to the Behavior, in the blue box. Student puts head down.

Annie: So, the Consequence is the green box? Task is removed or delayed...

JJ: Exactly. So in that example, the teacher gave a hard task, then the student put their head down instead of working on it, so then the teacher probably got sick of waiting for them to do the task and gave up on making them do it and removed the task.

Lin: Right, or the student continued to put their head down for so long that maybe the teacher just assigned it for homework, delaying the task.

Checking ABCs Understanding [id=fba2_abc_check]
----------------------------

Lin: Let's try applying this to Johnny's situation.

::fba2_abc_johnny [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Apply ABCs to Johnny"]

--- wait @fba2_abc_johnny_explanation.value ---

JJ: So using the ABCs, we know that: [face=explaining]

The antecedent was your roommate told him to go to bed.

The behavior was that he ran out of his room.

The consequence was that your roommate chased after him. His running around ultimately led to him not going to bed on time again.

::fba2_johnny_function [display=target:psych_sba_sidebar3auto label="Identify Johnny's Function"]

