Putting It Together [id=fba2_putting_together]
--------------------

Annie: Wow! Those are some great ideas for changing the antecedent conditions to prevent a behavior from occurring, especially when the function of the behavior is escape. [face=smile]

Lin: Okay -- let's put it all together. So we now know that our behavior modification plan should incorporate positive reinforcement for a desired behavior that addresses the function of the problem behavior of escape. We know that manipulating antecedent conditions is the way to go. We also know from last time that, in general, punishment should be avoided as a consequence.

Annie: That sounds hard. We've already gotten some great ideas, but I don't even know where to start. [face=fear]

JJ: Let's go back to the Competing Behavior Pathway organizer we started and use some of the strategies we've talked about so far.

